x4freetext: 5.5 MV Van de Graaff accelerator
~5 keV thickness for 4 MeV alpha-particles prepared
by vacuum evaporation of 26MgO on ~10 ug/cm2)
self-supporting carbon foils in a Si free vacuum
system.
To detect the scattered particles at lab.
angles 80, 118, 135, and 165 deg.
The incident beam was collected by means of a
Faraday cup and was measured using a current
integrator.
The absolute error in the alpha particle energy is
estimated to be +/- 5 to +/- 20 keV.
Compiled by DR B.M.JYRWA ,BARNALEE BAYON

x4freetext: The error on the measured absolute cross
sections (+/- 7% except at the minima in the
excitation functions where it would go up to +/-20%)
including
error in the normalizing factors consisting of:
- the target thickness,
- the solid angle, and
- the number of alpha particles incident, has been
estimated from the departure of the measured cross
sections in the range 2.95 to 3.2 MeV from Rutherford
cross sections (~+/-5%)
error due to counting statistics is
around +/- 5% on the average, going to +/- 20% at the
minima in the excitation functions.
